NAME: 100075.jpg || COMMENT: Image segmentation problem, based on image from the Berkeley Segmentation Dataset and Benchmark. Images are converted to graphs using the procedure from [Samuel de Sousa, Yll Haxhimusa, and Walter G. Kropatsch (2013). Estimation of Distribution Algorithm for the Max-Cut Problem. LNCS 7877, pp. 244-253]. In short, the image is split into regions of adjacent pixels with similar colors, and each region is a node in this graph. Adjacent regions with different colors have high weights, and adjacent regions with similar colors have negative weights.

LNCS 7877, pp. 244-253]. In short, the image is split into regions of adjacent pixels with similar colors, and each region is a node in this graph. Adjacent regions with different colors have high weights, and adjacent regions with similar colors have negative weights.
